      "source": [
        "### Introduction: Function and Slope from Derivative\n",
        "\n",
        "We have a function and want to get to the lowest point to minimize it.\n",
        "This represents our loss function which we want to minimize.\n",
        "\n",
        "We can use the derivative to find the slope of the function at any point.\n",
        "Naively, we can take a step down the slope to get closer to the minimum.\n",
        "This is our gradient, which we use to descend the function."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 79,
      "id": "c54c306b",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "c54c306b",
        "outputId": "f5595baf-9b0c-41d6-e16b-fd3381ed6242"
      },
