        "### Default functions"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "16c10254",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "$$\\begin{align*}\n",
        "L(x) &= x^2 + 0.5 * sin(5x)\\\\\n",
        "\\nabla_L(x) &= 2x + 2.5*cos(5x)\n",
        "\\end{align*}$$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 81,
      "id": "ab661704",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def loss_function(x):\n",
        "    return x**2 + 0.5*np.sin(5*x)\n",
        "\n",
        "def gradient(x):\n",
        "    return 2*x + 2.5*np.cos(5*x)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "aedaa138",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "aedaa138"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Gradient Descent"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "f5377e8c",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "f5377e8c"
      },
      "source": [
        "In gradient descent, you try to minimize a function $L$ by using the gradient $\\nabla L$ to follow the *slope* of the function. As such, you repeat the following iteration:\n",
        "$$\\begin{align*}\n",
        "    g_t &= \\nabla L(w_t)\\\\[5pt]\n",
        "    w_{t+1} &= w_t - \\eta\\cdot g_t\n",
        "\\end{align*}$$\n",
        "where $\\eta$ is the learning rate."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 82,
      "id": "68e55913",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "68e55913"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def gradient_descent(learning_rate, num_iterations=30, x_start=-2.0, gradient=gradient, loss_function=loss_function):\n",
        "    x = np.array(x_start)\n",
        "    losses = [loss_function(x)]\n",
        "    positions = [x]\n",
        "\n",
        "    for _ in range(num_iterations):\n",
        "        grad = np.array(gradient(x))\n",
        "        x = x - learning_rate * grad\n",
        "        losses.append(loss_function(x))\n",
        "        positions.append(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return positions, losses"
      ]
    },
