    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "69edfa28",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "69edfa28"
      },
      "source": [
        "### RMSProp"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "6306e2a3",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6306e2a3"
      },
      "source": [
        "In AdaGrad, $v_t$ is constantly growing. This can lead to a very small learning value, so the progress each round becomes minimal for high learning rates. RMSProp avoids this by using a moving average. For this, we introduce an additional parameter $\\beta$, which defines the importance of the accumulated averages versus the current gradient.\n",
        "$$\\begin{align*}\n",
        "    v_0 &= 0\\\\[2pt]\n",
        "    v_t &= \\beta v_{t-1} + (1-\\beta) g_t^2\\\\[5pt]\n",
        "    \\hat{v}_t &= \\frac{v_t}{1-\\beta^t}\\\\\n",
        "    w_{t+1} &= w_t - \\frac{\\eta}{\\sqrt{\\hat{v}_t}+\\epsilon} \\cdot g_t\n",
        "\\end{align*}$$\n",
        "$\\hat{v}_t$ is used to offset the bias created by the initial choice $v_0 = 0$."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 96,
      "id": "edf8a988",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "edf8a988"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "## Question: what does beta do?\n",
        "## Question: What happens if beta is 0?\n",
        "def RMSProp(learning_rate, num_iterations=30, x_start=-2.0, beta=0.5, gradient=gradient, loss_function=loss_function):\n",
        "    eps = 1e-16\n",
        "    x = np.array(x_start)\n",
        "    losses = [loss_function(x)]\n",
        "    positions = [x]\n",
        "    vt = 0\n",
        "    for t in range(1, num_iterations + 1):\n",
        "        grad = np.array(gradient(x))\n",
        "        vt = beta * vt + (1-beta) * grad**2\n",
        "        vt_bias = vt / (1-beta**t)\n",
        "        x = x - learning_rate * grad / (np.sqrt(vt_bias) + eps)\n",
        "        losses.append(loss_function(x))\n",
        "        positions.append(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return positions, losses"
      ]
    },
