    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "13aecd11",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "13aecd11"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Momentum"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "7b804c74",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7b804c74"
      },
      "source": [
        "Momentum takes a different approach from the previous versions by adding *momentum*. If we keep moving downhill in one direct, we \"speed up\" and take bigger steps. If we then hit a spot that descends in the opposite direction, we decelarate. In this case, the step size decreases, but the direction only changes if the slope of the point we hit is large enough.\n",
        "$$\\begin{align*}\n",
        "    m_0 &= 0\\\\[2pt]\n",
        "    m_t &= \\beta m_{t-1} + (1-\\beta) g_t\\\\[5pt]\n",
        "    \\hat{m}_t &= \\frac{m_t}{1-\\beta^t}\\\\\n",
        "    w_{t+1} &= w_t - \\eta\\cdot\\hat{m}_t\n",
        "\\end{align*}$$\n",
        "$\\hat{m}_t$ is used to offset the bias created by the initial choice $m_0 = 0$.\\\n",
        "Note that the gradient is now no longer squared, so $m_t$ can be negative."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 101,
      "id": "7804c846",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7804c846"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def momentum(learning_rate, num_iterations=30, x_start=-2.0, beta=0.5,  gradient=gradient, loss_function=loss_function):\n",
        "    x = np.array(x_start)\n",
        "    losses = [loss_function(x)]\n",
        "    positions = [x]\n",
        "    mt = 0\n",
        "    for t in range(1, num_iterations + 1):\n",
        "        grad = np.array(gradient(x))\n",
        "        mt = beta * mt + (1-beta) * grad\n",
        "        mt_bias = mt / (1-beta**t)\n",
        "        x = x - learning_rate * mt_bias\n",
        "        losses.append(loss_function(x))\n",
        "        positions.append(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return positions, losses"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 102,
      "id": "f31111b5",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def f_squared(x):\n",
        "    return x**2\n",
        "\n",
        "def grad_squared(x):\n",
        "    return 2*x"
      ]
    },
